news.title: One nautical mile of air space around Supertech twin towers briefly unavailable on Aug 28
news.para: The Union Ministry of Civil Aviation has given its consent for this, the Noida Authority said as it oversaw preparations for demolition of the nearly 100-metre-tall twin towers on Sunday.

news.title: Supertech twin towers: Roads to stay diverted on Aug 28, Google maps to have updates
news.para: "While several routes especially those leading to twin towers will have diversions from morning till evening, the Noida-Greater Noida Expressway will stay closed between 2 pm and 3 pm," DCP (Traffic) Ganesh Saha said as he and DCP (Central Noida) Rajesh S briefed reporters about the preparations for August 28.

news.title: '150%' confident of safely pulling down Supertech twin towers: Utkarsh Mehta, Edifice Engineering
news.para: The Mumbai-based Edifice Engineering has partnered with South Africa's Jet Demolitions for the high-risk job that involves razing two high-rise structures in a manner that the residential towers at barely nine-metre distance do not get affected.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM reviews preparations for demolition of Supertech twin towers
news.para: Water tankers, sprinklers and smog guns will be used to clear the dust generated as a result of demolition. Sweeping machines will be installed on the roads within two kilometre radius of the buildings.

news.title: Accountability will be fixed, if not today then tomorrow: Noida Authority CEO
news.para: The Supertech twin towers case is also a lesson for government officials, the senior IAS officer said, as legal action has been initiated against 26 Noida Authority officials for their involvement in the project.

news.title: SC says Supertech's twin towers buyers will be refunded in full, asks IRP to deposit Rs 1 crore
news.para: The apex court also asked the Interim Resolution Professional (IRP) of the firm, facing insolvency proceedings, to deposit Rs one crore with the apex court registry.

news.title: Maharashtra: No new buildings within 1km of SGNP, says forest department
news.para: Following the gazette notification of 2016, the state had set up a monitoring committee headed by BMC’s additional municipal commissioner (Projects) to sanction development works in the ESZ around Sanjay Gandhi National Park.

news.title: Mukesh Ambani is mystery buyer of $80 million villa in Dubai
news.para: The property on Palm Jumeirah was purchased earlier this year for Ambani’s youngest son, Anant, one of the people said, asking not to be named as the transaction is private.

news.title: Blackstone to raise $500 million through REIT IPO of Nexus Malls
news.para: Blackstone’s Indian retail portfolio, which is held through its Nexus Malls unit, could be valued at about $2.5 billion, the people said. The REIT could be listed as soon as 2023, they said.

news.title: DTCP bans sale of properties in 18 societies in Gurugram over licence rule violations
news.para: District town planner (enforcement) Amit Madholia said that action was taken against the 18 societies and notices have been pasted at the properties as per the directions from the DTCP director’s office.

news.title: China: Longfor Group prices $219 million bonds at a coupon rate of 3.3%
news.para: Longfor's three-year notes, priced at the lower end of an indicative range of 3% to 4.3%, were oversubscribed by 2.86 times, the company and market sources said. The offering was guaranteed by state-owned China Bond Insurance Co Ltd.

news.title: YES Bank leases 44,000 sq ft office space in Mumbai's Goregaon suburb
news.para: As per the lease agreement, the bank will be paying lease rental of Rs 53.19 lakh per month, taking its annual rental pay out to nearly Rs 6.40 crore. The bank has also paid security deposits worth nearly Rs 3.07 crore for the transaction.

news.title: UP RERA increases validity of registration of real estate agents to 10 years
news.para: Registered real estate agents in UP have been issued a "registration certificate" in Form-H prescribed in the UP RERA Rules. In this, the validity period of registration is five years. In Rule-10(3) of the UP Land Estate (Regulation and Development) Rules, 2016, the period of registration of a real estate agent has been fixed at 10 years.

news.title: HDFC Property Ventures, HDFC Venture Cap to be merged with HDFC Capital Advisors
news.para: The proposed scheme of amalgamation envisages merger of both the transferor companies with and into transferee company HDFC Capital Advisors and the dissolution of the transferor companies without being wound up.

news.title: Elan Group concludes 40 acre land deal with Indiabulls Real Estate in Gurugram
news.para: ​In January, the company had announced purchase of around 40 acres of land in Gurugram from Indiabulls Real Estate Ltd (IBREL) for Rs 580 crore for the development of housing and commercial projects.
